# Package Development
[Video 1](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=79s3z0gIuFU&list=PLk3B5c8iCV-T4LM0mwEyWIunIunLyEjqM)

File > New Project > New Directory > Create Package  

Creates:

* .Rbuildignore
* DESCRIPTION
* LICENSE
* man/
* NAMESPACE
* R/
* tester.Rproj

Add manually:

* man/hello.Rd
* R/hello.R

Build > Configure build tools

* Configure > select all
* Check package: `--as-cran`

Roxygen

* Code > insert roxygen skeleton
* Code > clean and rebuild
* Remove `man/hello.Rd` and `namespace`
* Add roxygen tags to `hello.R`
* Code > clean and rebuild
* Check
* Add `printer.R`
* `library(usethis)`
* `use_readme_rmd()`
* Add description from `DESCRIPTION`
* knit
* tools > version control > add & commit
* `use_github(protocol = "https")`

Import/Export functions

* Suggests: for vignette
* Imports: for building package ("safer" than Depends)
* Depends: [depends vs imports?](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/8637993/better-explanation-of-when-to-use-imports-depends)
* `usethis::use_package('utils')`
* `usethis::use_package('dpylr')`
* In `printer.R`: @importFrom utils, head
* In `printer.R`: @importFrom dplyr, select
